    • Constructor Detail

      • MessageProcessingInfo

        public MessageProcessingInfo(String messType)
        Create a default MessageProcessingInfo associated with the given message type.

        Default attributes are that the message is exposed and internal message processing is enabled.

        Parameters:
        messType - a message type

      • isExposed

        public boolean isExposed()
        Is this message type passed up to the application?

        By default, administrative messages such as Heartbeats are not passed up to the application .

        Returns:
        true if the application sees this message.

      • isInternalProcessingEnabled

        public boolean isInternalProcessingEnabled()
        Is this message processed internally by Catalys?

        Some messages, notably administrative messages, are processed automatically by Catalys. For example, in response to a TestRequest message, Catalys will automatically send out a Heartbeat.

        Returns:
        false if special Catalys message processing has been disabled.

      • setExposed

        public void setExposed(boolean value)
        Determines whether or not this message will be passed up by a session's getMessage method.

        Side effect:
        Setting exposed false will automatically enable internal processing.
        If you want to both hide a message type and disable processing (a dangerous thing to do because no-one will process the message in that case), call the methods in this order: 

         setExposed( false )
 setInternalProcessingEnabled( false )
        Parameters:
        value - if true message will be seen by application.

      • setInternalProcessingEnabled

        public void setInternalProcessingEnabled(boolean value)
        Catalys's internal processing of messages can be disabled by this method.
        This includes the automatic processing of administrative messages as defined by the FIX protocol.

        Warning:
        Disabling Catalys's automatic processing can stop the protocol working properly.

        Parameters:
        value - true if normal processing is enabled.
